cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with recognizing human-object interactions using a new pairwise body-part attention model. This falls under the domain of computer vision, making cs.CV the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed approach involves attention-based feature selection and feature representation scheme, which are techniques commonly used in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The pairwise body-part attention model is a machine learning model that learns to focus on crucial body parts and their correlations. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The HICO dataset used in the paper contains images and annotations, which are multimedia data. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The concept of recognizing human-object interactions can be applied in robotics, making cs.RO a possible sub-category.
